cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a deep learning method for accurate mandible segmentation in CT scans, which involves image processing and computer vision techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses recurrent neural networks (RNN) and convolutional neural networks (CNN), which are popular machine learning techniques for sequence modeling and image analysis, respectively. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely categories. Additionally, the paper deals with medical imaging, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) categories.
